  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://w3id.org/noria/ontology/troubleTicketNoteCorrelatedExecution">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty"/>
    <rdfs:label>troubleTicketNoteCorrelatedExecution</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">The correlated *ProcedureExecutionContainer* corresponding to the corrective maintenance actions depicted in the Trouble Ticket Note (i.e. the set of `EventRecord` about interactions with the system and as notified by the system).

From a practical perspective, relating a `noria:TroubleTicketNote` to a `pep:ProcedureExecutionContainer` is akin to show off the materialization of a corrective maintenance action from the technical perspective.
Note that for actions undoubtedly related to a given trouble ticket note (i.e. that can be asserted without mining for execution context candidates), one can avoid using `troubleTicketNoteCorrelatedExecution` by directly relating the note to `EventRecord` with `ldp:member` as `TroubleTicket` and `TroubleTicketNote` are themselves subclasses of `pep:ProcedureExecutionContainer`.
</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/noria/ontology/TroubleTicketNote"/>
    <rdfs:range rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/pep/ProcedureExecutionContainer"/>
    <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://purl.org/dc/terms/relation"/>
    <vs:term_status>unstable</vs:term_status>
    <skos:changeNote>Changes in v0.2:
- Adding the troubleTicketNoteCorrelatedExecution property.
</skos:changeNote>
    <rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/noria/ontology/"/>
  </rdf:Description>
